    "description": "Motion design used to cost $5,000 and 2 weeks. \n\nNow it’s a 3-step pipeline inside Claude Code.\n\n→ Pull visual references with the Pinterest API \n→ Storyboard 6 scenes via GPT Images 2.0 in Higgsfield MCP \n→ Drop the board straight into Seedance 2.0\n\nBrief to rendered video. No agency. No back-and-forth. No timeline that bleeds into next month.\n\nThis is what the Higgsfield MCP update actually unlocks — an end-to-end motion design workflow that runs inside your terminal.\n\nIf you’re still outsourcing motion design in 2026, you’re paying for something you can now automate.\n\nSave this before your competitors do.\n#claudeai #motiongraphic #higgsfield",
